  "body": "### Summary\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Problem\r\nWe are using three subscriptions for accessing a single `customization-color` property, in chat, communities & shell screens.\r\nWe should use a single subscription, it will be best if we move this subscription to the child(where it is used), so the whole view doesn't rerender when the value changes.\r\n\r\nLike in the below case, move subscription to the shell function and also create a separate function for `[quo/floating-shell-button` and use it there.\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/17097240/46a66d4c-5771-4f4f-b339-0cd4fc3c5be3)\r\n\r\n\r\nrelated to changes in https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/pull/15860 cc @jo-mut \r\n",
